01:27:37,062 --> 01:27:38,154
<i>Yeah.</i>

1459
01:27:38,663 --> 01:27:42,155
<i>No. She turns around
and comes running back, right?</i>

1460
01:27:42,400 --> 01:27:44,925
<i>Nope. She got on that plane
and flew to Paris.</i>

1461
01:27:45,337 --> 01:27:47,168
<i>And he went after her.</i>

1462
01:27:47,405 --> 01:27:51,171
<i>No. He got on another plane
to do a game in Sacramento.</i>

1463
01:27:52,511 --> 01:27:53,910
That's how it ends?

1464
01:27:55,347 --> 01:27:57,577
That was what? Four months ago.

1465
01:27:58,083 --> 01:27:59,175
Now Mickey's...

1466
01:27:59,351 --> 01:28:02,252
<i>...alone in the house
he didn't want and he's...</i>

1467
01:28:02,420 --> 01:28:04,684
<i>...you know, adjusting. Slowly.</i>

1468
01:28:05,023 --> 01:28:08,356
<i>''April in Paris</i>

1469
01:28:12,197 --> 01:28:15,530
<i>''Chestnuts in blossom</i>

1470
01:28:19,538 --> 01:28:22,939
<i>''Holiday tables...</i>

1471
01:28:24,109 --> 01:28:27,442
<i>''...under the trees</i>

1472
01:28:33,785 --> 01:28:37,118
<i>''April in Paris</i>

1473
01:28:40,492 --> 01:28:44,588
<i>''This is a feeling</i>

1474
01:28:48,133 --> 01:28:50,966
<i>''No one can ever...</i>

1475
01:28:54,239 --> 01:28:56,833
<i>''...reprieve''</i>

1476
01:28:56,908 --> 01:28:57,932
<i>And Ellen?</i>

1477
01:28:58,009 --> 01:29:01,103
<i>I spoke to her about a month ago
in Paris, and...</i>

1478
01:29:01,580 --> 01:29:03,309
<i>...she was lonely and...</i>

1479
01:29:03,481 --> 01:29:04,641
<i>...you know...</i>

1480
01:29:06,585 --> 01:29:08,075
<i>...not bad.</i>

1481
01:29:08,520 --> 01:29:12,354
<i>But you know when you talk to someone
and they say they're fine...</i>

1482
01:29:12,724 --> 01:29:16,125
<i>...but you hear that thing in their voice
and you know they're not?</i>

1483
01:29:16,261 --> 01:29:17,922
<i>You know that thing?</i>

1484
01:29:18,430 --> 01:29:19,920
<i>She's got it.</i>

1485
01:29:23,335 --> 01:29:27,669
<i>''Never missed a warm embrace</i>

1486
01:29:29,507 --> 01:29:33,841
<i>''Till April in Paris</i>

1487
01:29:37,048 --> 01:29:40,711
<i>''Who can I run to?</i>

1488
01:29:44,189 --> 01:29:47,625
<i>''What have you done to...</i>

1489
01:29:49,794 --> 01:29:53,025
<i>''...my heart?''</i>

1490
01:30:04,309 --> 01:30:06,038
Oh, I’m ill.

1491
01:30:06,511 --> 01:30:09,503
lmagine if l actually knew them
how sick I’d be.

1492
01:30:10,649 --> 01:30:12,640
That's not going to be us.

1493
01:30:16,554 --> 01:30:19,489
Can we order?
My stomach's doing the conga.

1494
01:30:19,724 --> 01:30:21,316
- The warmth.
- I’m hungry.

1495
01:30:21,493 --> 01:30:24,621
He's right. Let's get this party going.
Waiter?

1496
01:30:26,398 --> 01:30:29,162
Would you like a breakfast menu perhaps?

1497
01:30:29,768 --> 01:30:32,601
l know, it's late.
We're waiting for someone.

1498
01:30:32,771 --> 01:30:36,764
You know what happened
at the Knick game? Did they go overtime?

1499
01:30:37,008 --> 01:30:38,839
Our friend is unbelievably late.

1500
01:30:39,244 --> 01:30:44,045
<i>Those people were at the game
and they've been there for over 30 minutes.</i>

1501
01:30:44,683 --> 01:30:45,581
Well...

1502
01:30:45,917 --> 01:30:48,249
...bring us the best champagne you got.

1503
01:30:50,322 --> 01:30:52,483
- Champagne.
- We're getting married.

1504
01:30:54,192 --> 01:30:57,423
You people want to know
what happened at the Knick game?

1505
01:30:59,431 --> 01:31:00,864
Weird game.

1506
01:31:01,032 --> 01:31:03,432
l never saw something like this in my life.

1507
01:31:03,501 --> 01:31:04,934
What happened?

1508
01:31:06,037 --> 01:31:07,299
lt was incredible.

1509
01:31:07,472 --> 01:31:09,463
We're waiting for the anthem to start.

1510
01:31:12,610 --> 01:31:14,271
Are you all right tonight?

1511
01:31:15,313 --> 01:31:17,042
- Are you okay?
- I’m fine.

1512
01:31:17,115 --> 01:31:19,709
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, please rise...</i>

1513
01:31:19,818 --> 01:31:22,548
<i>...as we honour America
with our national anthem.</i>

1514
01:31:23,388 --> 01:31:26,221
<i>Please welcome David Sanborn.</i>

1515
01:31:52,484 --> 01:31:54,418
- What?
- l can't do the game.

1516
01:31:54,586 --> 01:31:56,417
- You sick?
- l must catch a plane.

1517
01:31:56,488 --> 01:31:57,580
- To where?
- Paris.

1518
01:31:57,655 --> 01:31:59,748
Now? No, you can't do that.

1519
01:32:00,125 --> 01:32:03,686
l won't let you go.
They'll throw you out of the league.

1520
01:32:03,928 --> 01:32:05,486
lf they do, they do.

1521
01:32:28,720 --> 01:32:30,449
l don't believe this.

1522
01:32:30,855 --> 01:32:33,187
- l was on my way to see you.
- Come on.

1523
01:32:33,525 --> 01:32:36,619
No, l swear. l was on my way to Paris.

1524
01:32:36,961 --> 01:32:39,930
Oh, forget Paris. l hated Paris.

1525
01:32:43,468 --> 01:32:45,800
What's the answer? Why will it work...

1526
01:32:45,870 --> 01:32:46,962
...this time?

1527
01:32:47,138 --> 01:32:48,469
l don't know.

1528
01:32:49,207 --> 01:32:51,869
l know we're better together
than we are apart.

1529
01:32:53,211 --> 01:32:54,872
And l'll move to Dallas...

1530
01:32:55,313 --> 01:32:59,807
...or Paris or the dark side of the moon,
because home is wherever you are.

1531
01:33:02,020 --> 01:33:03,544
And l also know...

1532
01:33:04,722 --> 01:33:06,155
...l love you.

1533
01:33:08,993 --> 01:33:10,984
So, tell me the truth.

1534
01:33:11,229 --> 01:33:13,163
Do you think we'll make it?

1535
01:33:17,735 --> 01:33:19,168
Piece of cake.

1536
01:33:41,459 --> 01:33:43,188
Then the Knicks lost.

1537
01:33:43,595 --> 01:33:44,926
They stink.

1538
01:33:45,730 --> 01:33:49,222
Well, let me get back to my food.
Have a good night.

1539
01:33:53,438 --> 01:33:56,669
lt's her. l know it's her.

1540
01:33:56,941 --> 01:33:58,932
lt's meant to be.

1541
01:34:01,980 --> 01:34:04,642
Why does every woman you're with
end up crying?

1542
01:34:07,552 --> 01:34:08,712
lt's them.

1543
01:34:18,296 --> 01:34:19,354
Ellen and Mickey.

1544
01:34:19,430 --> 01:34:21,159
Nice to meet you. You okay?

1545
01:34:21,299 --> 01:34:23,130
- Oh, yeah.
- You are.

1546
01:34:23,301 --> 01:34:25,064
- She'll be fine.
- Congratulations.

1547
01:34:25,236 --> 01:34:26,464
Look who's here.

1548
01:34:32,577 --> 01:34:37,480
Champagne. Best we got. lt's like me:
bubbly and dying to go home.

1549
01:34:38,149 --> 01:34:40,208
l would like to make a toast.

1550
01:34:41,653 --> 01:34:43,086
To my father...

1551
01:34:44,189 --> 01:34:46,180
...who did one really great thing.

1552
01:34:46,257 --> 01:34:47,815
He brought us together.

1553
01:34:49,861 --> 01:34:51,328
To marriage.

1554
01:34:53,565 --> 01:34:54,554
Let's eat.

1555
01:34:55,900 --> 01:34:58,869
Sounds good to me.
Young fellow, you first.

1556
01:34:59,404 --> 01:35:00,735
Me? Oh, okay.

1557
01:35:03,141 --> 01:35:05,371
l know exactly what l'll have.

1558
01:35:05,910 --> 01:35:07,741
l would like the veal...

1559
01:35:10,181 --> 01:35:11,273
...piccata.

1560
01:35:16,187 --> 01:35:20,453
What the hell! Me too. I’m done with this.
I’m eating tonight.

1561
01:35:20,625 --> 01:35:22,183
- Veal parmesan.
- Me too.

1562
01:35:22,360 --> 01:35:23,850
The blonde. Seven piccatas.

1563
01:35:24,028 --> 01:35:25,620
Liz, you must not know what...

1564
01:35:25,697 --> 01:35:29,189
...the toast is about.
When Mickey's father passed away...

1565
01:35:29,267 --> 01:35:32,703
...he wanted to be buried in France.
l was working in Paris.

1566
01:35:33,538 --> 01:35:35,699
You don't know that that's a true story.

1567
01:35:35,873 --> 01:35:39,309
Helen, this is all veal.
Seven piccata, one parmesan.

1568
01:35:39,544 --> 01:35:42,206
Fire it right up. l got a hungry group here.

1569
01:35:42,313 --> 01:35:46,807
For two days it was lost in Switzerland
and Ellen found it.

1570
01:35:46,985 --> 01:35:50,716
That's true. That's how we met.
You know that story, don't you?

